snippet.title: Amber Heard Joins SAMS Women's Mission to Lebanon, February 2019
snippet.description:
Last month, SAMS Goodwill Ambassador #AmberHeard joined our women’s health mission to #Lebanon, meeting with Syrian refugee women and underserved local communities who have limited access to the treatment they need. Amber has long advocated for women’s empowerment and ensuring the voices of those in need are amplified across the world.

During her visit, Amber visited informal settlements for Syrian refugees living in the Beka’a Valley and a local hospital in Tripoli where SAMS Volunteers treated 812 patients, performed 77 surgeries in addition to providing 166 cervical cancer screenings for women struggling to access these lifesaving services, free of charge.

Learn more about Amber's trip to Lebanon in the video below!
